headline: These Were the Best and Worst S&P 500 Stocks During Trump’s First 100 Days
summary: All three major U.S. indexes were nursing hefty losses since Inauguration Day on Jan. 20.  The S&P 500 and Dow Jones Industrial Average have fallen 7.8% and 7.5% since then, respectively.  The tech-heavy Nasdaq Composite has declined 11.5%.
